; Node 22+ exposes an experimental `localStorage` global that is not a real
; Storage object — it's an empty `{}` unless `--localstorage-file` is set.
; `@vue/devtools-kit` (pulled in by `vite-plugin-vue-devtools`) calls
; `localStorage.getItem(...)` during Vite config load and crashes. Disable the
; experimental API so `localStorage` is undefined and the library skips it.
node-options=--no-experimental-webstorage
